Two types of enums exists in xenon, a classic enum and a type enum. They are declared slightly differently: // classic enum
type ReturnType = < OK = 0 | ERROR = 84
>; let status: ReturnType = OK; // type enum (would require a definition of Dog and Cat)
type AnimalType = < DOG: Dog | CAT: Cat
>; let animal: AnimalType = DOG;
